title: Random blue border added during training preprocessing
body:
During training, a [random blue border](https://github.com/ildoonet/tf-pose-estimation/blob/master/tf_pose/pose_augment.py#L84-L90) is attached to every image in order to fit the target size criterion:

```
    if neww < _network_w or newh < _network_h:
        pw = max(0, (_network_w - neww) // 2)
        ph = max(0, (_network_h - newh) // 2)
        mw = (_network_w - neww) % 2
        mh = (_network_h - newh) % 2
        color = random.randint(0, 255)
        dst = cv2.copyMakeBorder(dst, ph, ph+mh, pw, pw+mw, cv2.BORDER_CONSTANT, value=(color, 0, 0))

```
![Screenshot from 2020-01-03 15-11-23](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3956593/71728104-7d1a1c00-2e3c-11ea-8fe7-97a29ac2d266.png)

I assume the border should rather be filled with the value that is used for mean subtraction (127, 127, 127) or a random color, but random blue sounds wrong.
